	<h2>Links to other on-line Axis & Allies resources:</h2>
<p>	These other sites relate to all aspects of Axis and Allies, clarifying rules, offering downloads, other odds calculators, and discussions of strategy. There are a lot more out there, but I find these to be the most useful:</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://axisandallies.org/">AxisandAllies.org</a>- this is my favourite forum for discussing Axis & Allies. Great community.</li> 
	<li><a href="http://www.gametableonline.com/">Game Table Online</a> - online site to play A&A (free vs AI, or one-time-pay-to-activate vs other users). Great community.</li>
	<li><a href="http://triplea.sourceforge.net/mywiki/TripleA">TripleA</a> - turn based strategy game for playing online A&A-like style games (free). Great community.</li>
	<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Axis_and_Allies">Axis & Allies Wikipedia article</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://www.wizards.com/Company/Brands/AxisandAllies.aspx">Wizards of the Coast (WOC), Axis & Allies</a> - official site.</li>
	<li><a href="http://games.groups.yahoo.com/group/axisandallies/">Axis & Allies (A Yahoo! group)</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=ah/faqs/axisrevised">WOC's Axis & Allies Revised Rules FAQ</a> - clarifies some of the commonly confused rules.</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.wizards.com/avalonhill/rules/AxAl-AnEd_Rules.pdf">A&A 50th Anniversary Edition rule book</a> (3.1 MB PDF)</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.wizards.com/avalonhill/rules/axis2004.pdf">Revised Edition A&A rule book</a> (8.7 MB PDF)</li>
	<li><a href="http://pages.videotron.ca/silexmt/optoaster/main.html">Operation Toaster</a> - Silex's AA page</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.dskelly.com/misc/aa/aasim.html">David Skelly's Axis & Allies Combat Simulator/Calculator</a> - simpler, but with more ruleset options. Also available on iPhone and Android.</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.twmacinta.com/myjava/allies/">Java Battle Simulator for Axis & Allies</a> - simpler, but faster, good for checking the accuracy of AACalc</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.cascadiatechnology.com/westfront/content/tools/calculatorj.htm">WestFront's web-based calculator</a></li>
</ul>
